<longDescription>The application uses an anchor tag whose `target` attribute is set to `_blank`, but the `rel` attribute is not set with the `noopener` value. The page opened from that target link may have the access to the `location` object of the original page through `window.opener.location`. A malicious page associated with this link will be able to navigate the original page to an arbitrary site, such as a phishing site, and thus, execute a reverse tabnabbing attack.
Note that most contemporary browsers add the `noopener` value to the `rel` automatically by default. Thus, only users with older versions of browsers are targets for this phishing attack.</longDescription>
<securityKind>true</securityKind>
